Notes.Text:
This update for python3 fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2022-37454: Fixed a buffer overflow in hashlib.sha3_* implementations. (bsc#1204577)
- CVE-2020-10735: Fixed a bug to limit amount of digits converting text to int and vice vera. (bsc#1203125)

Vulnerabilities.Description: A flaw was found in python. In algorithms with quadratic time complexity using non-binary bases, when using int("text"), a system could take 50ms to parse an int string with 100,000 digits and 5s for 1,000,000 digits (float, decimal, int.from_bytes(), and int() for binary bases 2, 4, 8, 16, and 32 are not affected). The highest threat from this vulnerability is to system availability.
